
Overview of noun care

The noun care has 6 senses (first 6 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (9) care, attention, aid, tending -- (the work of providing treatment for or attending to someone or something; "no medical care was required"; "the old car needs constant attention")
2. (4) caution, precaution, care, forethought -- (judiciousness in avoiding harm or danger; "he exercised caution in opening the door"; "he handled the vase with care")
3. (1) concern, care, fear -- (an anxious feeling; "care had aged him"; "they hushed it up out of fear of public reaction")
4. (1) care -- (a cause for feeling concern; "his major care was the illness of his wife")
5. (1) care, charge, tutelage, guardianship -- (attention and management implying responsibility for safety; "he is in the care of a bodyguard")
6. (1) care, maintenance, upkeep -- (activity involved in maintaining something in good working order; "he wrote the manual on car care")

